
#################################################################################
# 
# Memory Generator (Memaker) Installation Guideline
#
# Purpose:
#  The installation guideline will help you to install memory generator (memaker).
#  After extracting the compressed file, please follow the below instruction to
#  install the memory generator.
#
###################################################################################

Installation stage:

1. Extract the compressed file
   Please change directory to the hierarchy where the memory generator is to be installed.
   >gzip -d FSF0L_Memaker_200901.2.1.tar.gz ; tar xvf FSF0L_Memaker_200901.2.1.tar

2. Setup your ITC environment in memaker.env
   Please edit your ITC environment as your install path.
   Please refer the header of "memaker.env" to get more detailed information.
   >vi memaker.env
   >source memaker.env

3. Save your license file
   >cp memaker.dat $ITC/flexlm/license/.

4. Launch your license server.  
   Please refer to Memaker User Manual to know the license launch instructions in details.
   You can find this manual from $ITC/EXE/memaker.package/doc/Memaker_UserGuide_200901.2.1.pdf

5. Setup your display environment (optional)
   The memory generator is performed by GUI (Graphic User Interface). So, 
   before using memory generator, please setup your display environment. 

6. Execute memory generator
   >memaker


